    "name": "Dianne Mower",
    "profile": "American Jazz Singer & Songwriter \r\n\r\nBorn and Raised in Patterson, New Jersey on February 13th,1953. Her mother was a classical singer. \r\n\r\nShe started her career at the age of 17 singing in top 40 lounges across the East Coast where she developed her ability to communicate with an audience, a skill that would become a trademark for her inimate style. \r\n\r\nMower would later build a reputation when she joined the highly acclaimed jazz vocal quartet, Jasmine where she would tour extensively and solidify her style from energetic bops to satin blues \r\n\r\nAs a jazz singer with experience in nightclubs, Dianne would perform in clubs from New York to Hawaii often sharing the stage with such jazz legends such as [a300694], [a303410], [a37737], & [a253478]. \r\n\r\nShe is also a celebrated lyricist, recieving praise from [a37737] and penning many of his tunes including Unsquare Dance, Three To Get Ready, & Cable Car. She has also collaborated with [a2919352] to add the lyrics to [a254945]'s Blue Bos",
